{
  "stem": "9168.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in my case, somehow I became very friendly [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] with a Hawaiian court reporter, Piulani Ahuna of Honolulu, whose folks were educators in Hawaii, and claimed to be one of the-- the only remaining 88 pure-blooded Hawaiian families.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And especially Siegfried Ramler, who was born in Jerusalem, educated in London, spoke eight languages fluently who was an interpreter.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were several other reporters, maybe five or six of us, who became very friendly.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we also bonded with some of the international press, became very friendly with the BBC reporter I told you about.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were several others-- So we-- yes, we did.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had this group.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think they were not only maybe Allied personnel who were able to get passes to the courtroom, but German citizens.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They wanted-- I think they wanted to have German citizens, who had never been members of the Nazi party, who had been cleared of Nazism, in the courtroom to hear what we all were going to hear.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the-- the international press.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a tremendous international press team there, and they were seated in the regular audience section.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was this-- this special-- I think that I have that right.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I know there was a balcony built.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I believe the balcony was for the-- the private-- public, not private, but public people who were admitted to the courtroom, and that the lower level was the international press.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That area was not a really large area.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The courtroom was just taken up with all of the defendants and the counsel, American teams, defense attorneys.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
